          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZS9fhu3rxhFvU7mxqwDdyG1AFHslfWrf0t-06UzB3zcJkj4z2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "At arrival I went thru the app thru my phone to notify staff that I was on site. I read that pickup would be at photo section. I locked the app indicating that I have arrived. The phone went off and the cashier from the main line pickup phone that rang and walked away. A discussion withy the customer asking what that was about. The cashier mentioned that for a pickup. Customer goes back and forth with cashier indicating don\u2019t they know there a line. If the location. Is short staff they should have a sign indicating pickup by main cashier line. At optimal working conditions you have enough staff but when you don\u2019t just indication other options. It would also would have been nice to indicate that if I could step over to the main cashier line since they are short staff rather than ignoring me. Next issue my order did not fit in one bag it required two bag and it over flowing. Asking me if I need another bag when I already paid for bag at checkout is crazy. In the future I would rather return items than Pay for additional bags that I paid for during my online pickup check out. You can see from picture that no one would be able to hold the bag packed in this manner. This is management at this location not teaching the staff how to properly pack store pickups.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNUakpfUHZBRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x96f53d3afad9fa25!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICTjJ_PvAE%7C%7C?hl=en",
